        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 6 at 7:41AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Patchy fog dense fog has developed over the north and east
portions of the Helena Valley and along sections of highway 287
bordering Canyon Ferry Lake. This will continue for the next
couple of hours and may even expand in coverage before
dissipating later this morning.

Those traveling near the Helena Valley and along highway 287 in
between Three Forks and Helena should be prepared for highly
variable conditions across short distances with visibility
falling as low as a half mile or less. Slow down and allow extra
time to reach your destination.
</description>
